        <num>Chapter 59-2</num>
        <heading>Property Tax Act</heading>
        <section eId="sec_59_2_208">
          <num>59-2-208</num>
          <heading>Duties of commission and county auditors relative to mines.</heading>
          <content>
            <p>59-2-208.
Duties of commission and county auditors relative to mines.
The duties of the commission and county auditors relative to:
(1)
the assessment of mines, mining claims, and mining property;
(2)
the statements and returns to be made; and
(3)
the equalization thereof are the same as those provided for the assessment of public utilities.
Enacted by Chapter
4
, 1987 General Session</p>
          </content>
          <subsection eId="59_2_208__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>the assessment of mines, mining claims, and mining property;</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="59_2_208__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>the statements and returns to be made; and</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="59_2_208__subsec_3">
            <num>(3)</num>
            <content>
              <p>the equalization thereof are the same as those provided for the assessment of public utilities.</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
        </section>
